Main Configuration Files
	httpd.conf | apache2.conf: The primary configuration file for Apache. It contains global settings, module loading, and other directives.
	ports.conf: Specifies the ports Apache listens on (common in Debian/Ubuntu).
	sites-available/: Directory containing configuration files for individual sites.
	sites-enabled/: Directory containing symbolic links to enabled sites from sites-available/.
	conf-available/: Additional configuration files (Debian/Ubuntu).
	conf-enabled/: Enabled configuration files (Debian/Ubuntu).
	.htaccess: Per-directory configuration files that override global settings.

====================================================================
path of configuration 
	/etc/apache2/apache2.conf
	Virtual hosts are in 
		/etc/apache2/sites-available/
	Modules: 
		/etc/apache2/mods-enabled/
	Logs: 
		/var/log/apache2/
	DocumentRoot
		/var/www/html
	context 
		Server config 
			Affects the entire server configuration.
			Overrides: Most other contexts except .htaccess when allowed
			httpd.conf
		Virtual host
			Defines settings for specific domains or IP-based configurations.
			Overrides global settings within the virtual host scope.
			inside ---><VirtualHost>
		Directory
			Applies settings to a specific directory and its contents.
			Higher priority than VirtualHost but lower than .htaccess.
			used inside <Directory>, <Location>, <Files>,<Proxy>
		.htaccess
			Applies settings at the directory level.
			Overrides Directory and VirtualHost when AllowOverride is enabled.
			inside per-directory .htaccess files
		
=====================================================================

	
